  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Deserialization of untrusted data can occur in versions 0.17.0 to 1.14.2 of the client SDK of Allegro AI\u2019s ClearML platform, enabling a maliciously uploaded artifact to run arbitrary code on an end user\u2019s system when interacted with.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2024-24590 describes a deserialization vulnerability in Allegro AI ClearML client SDK (versions 0.17.0\u20131.14.2) that enables arbitrary code execution via a maliciously uploaded artifact. This directly concerns software used in AI/ML workflows (AI tooling, model management, and MLOps pipelines) and impacts the software supply chain of general-purpose AI systems. It is a security vulnerability (RCE) with explicit evidence in CVSS/CWE entries."
  },
